-- Kan Seeks Support of New Komeito, Your Party in Upper House, Yomiuri Says
-- Kazuyo Sawa
-- 2010-07-12T22:24:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/kan-seeks-support-of-new-komeito-your-party-in-upper-house-yomiuri-says.html

          
          
             Japanâ€™s Prime Minister Naoto Kan
will seek the support of New Komeito and Your Party in passing
legislation with the possibility of forming a coalition in the
future, the Yomiuri newspaper reported, without citing anyone.  
 The ruling Democratic Party of Japan needs 12 more votes in
the upper house of parliament for a majority, the report said.
New Komeito has 19 seats, and Your Party has 11 seats, the
newspaper said.                  
